8 SECTION 1. ORS 339.250 is amended to read:
9 339.250. (1) Public school students shall comply with rules for the government of such schools,
10 pursue the prescribed course of study, use the prescribed textbooks and submit to the teachers’ au-
11 thority.
12 (2) Each district school board shall adopt written policies for the discipline, suspension or ex-
13 pulsion of any refractory student. The policies:
14 (a) May allow discipline, suspension or expulsion for conduct that includes, but is not limited
15 to:
16 (A) Willful disobedience;
17 (B) Open defiance of the authority of a school employee;
18 (C) Disruptive behavior;
19 [(C)] (D) Possession or distribution of tobacco, alcohol, drugs or other controlled substances;
20 [(D)] (E) Use or display of profane or obscene language;
21 [(E)] (F) Willful damage or injury to school property;
22 [(F)] (G) Use of threats, intimidation, harassment or coercion against a student or a school
23 employee;
24 [(G)] (H) Assault of a school employee or another student; or
