29 this subsection or any requirements established by rule under paragraph (a) of this subsection or
30 subparagraph (A) of this paragraph.
31 (C) When establishing requirements under this paragraph, the board or a school district or
32 public charter school shall attempt not to establish requirements that may discourage access to or
33 participation in the International Baccalaureate program.
34 (3)(a) In addition to the credit requirements described in subsection (2) of this section
35 and any other requirements established by the State Board of Education or by a school dis-
36 trict or public charter school, the board shall adopt proficiency standards for Essential
37 Learning Skills that must be demonstrated before a student is awarded a high school diploma
38 or a modified diploma. The proficiency standards must be demonstrated for, at a minimum,
39 the following:
40 (A) Reading and comprehending a variety of text;
41 (B) Writing clearly and accurately; and
42 (C) Applying mathematics in a variety of settings.
43 (b) The board shall adopt by rule assessment options for students to demonstrate profi-
44 ciency in Essential Learning Skills, as provided by paragraph (a) of this subsection.
45 [(3)] (c) A student providing work samples to demonstrate proficiency in Essential Learning
[10]

SB 1572
1 Skills [as may be required under subsection (2) of this section] must be allowed to use accommodations
2 described in the student’s individualized education program or the student’s plan developed in ac-
3 cordance with section 504 of the Rehabilitation Act of 1973, 29 U.S.C. 794. As used in this
4 [subsection] paragraph, the term “accommodations”:
5 [(a)] (A) Includes, but is not limited to:
6 [(A)] (i) Additional time to demonstrate proficiency.
7 [(B)] (ii) The ability to demonstrate proficiency in an alternative location that is secure and
8 proctored.
9 [(C)] (iii) The use of text-to-speech or speech-to-text technology or other assistive technology.
10 [(b)] (B) Does not include modifications that lower the proficiency standards or that are used
11 solely to earn modified credit.
12 (4) A student may satisfy the requirements of [subsection (2)] subsections (2) and (3) of this
