30 consent may not be used to allow a student to satisfy the requirements of subsection (7), (8) or (9)
31 of this section in less than three years.
32 (c) A copy of all consents provided under this subsection for students in a school district must
33 be forwarded to the district superintendent.
34 (d) Each school district must provide to the Superintendent of Public Instruction information
35 about the number of consents provided during a school year.
36 (12)(a) A student who qualifies to receive or receives a modified diploma, an extended diploma
